Gauteng police have launched an investigation after Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa’s bodyguard was hijacked in Olievenhoutbosch on Saturday night. The bodyguard, who is an SANDF official, was reportedly also robbed of several firearms; three assault rifles and three handguns. The hijackers allegedly drove around with the bodyguard for several hours and later dropped him off in Midrand. The car, a white BMW X6 SUV and two firearms were later found in Daveyton. The driver was the only person in the vehicle at the time of the incident. -TNA Reporter